        "description": {
            "value": "<p>As a swashbuckler at the peak of your skill, you swell with confidence and bravado in every attack. Your proficiency rank for your swashbuckler class DC increases to master.</p>\n<p>When you Strike as part of a finisher or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Opportune Riposte], you can give the Strike the failure effect from the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Confident Finisher] action, including the increase from @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.Precise Finisher] if you have that feat.</p>\n<p>You can do so only if the Strike uses a weapon or unarmed attack that you could use for Confident Finisher.</p>"
